sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Client as Frontend
    participant Server as Express Server
    participant Middleware as Auth/Rate Limiting
    participant Queue as P-Queue (Task Queue)
    participant Service as AI Service (Freepik/Google)
    participant External as External API

    %% Initial Request Phase
    Client->>Server: POST /api/generate-* (e.g. image/video)
    Server->>Middleware: Verify Token & Check Limits
    alt Rate limit exceeded or Unauthorized
        Middleware--xClient: 401/429 Error
    else Request valid
        Middleware->>Server: Proceed
    end

    %% Queueing Phase
    Server->>Queue: generateQueue.add(task)
    Note over Queue: Concurrency limit (e.g. 5)<br/>Prevents overloading external APIs
    
    %% Execution Phase
    Queue->>Service: Execute task (e.g. generateImage)
    Service->>External: POST Request with API Key
    External-->>Service: 202 Accepted + Task ID
    Service-->>Queue: Task ID
    Queue-->>Server: Task ID
    Server-->>Client: 200 OK (status: "in_progress", task_id)

    %% Polling Phase
    loop Every 2-5 seconds
        Client->>Server: GET /api/status/:taskId
        Server->>Service: getTaskStatus(taskId)
        Service->>External: GET /status/:taskId
        
        alt Task still processing
            External-->>Service: status: "in_progress"
            Service-->>Server: status: "in_progress"
            Server-->>Client: 200 OK (status: "in_progress")
        else Task completed
            External-->>Service: status: "completed" + Asset URLs
            Service-->>Server: status: "completed" + Asset URLs
            Server-->>Client: 200 OK (status: "completed", url: "...")
        else Task failed
            External-->>Service: status: "failed" + Error Reason
            Service-->>Server: status: "failed" + Error Reason
            Server-->>Client: 400/500 Error
        end
    end
